# 06 Audit Logging and Monitoring

## Intent
Provide accountable, tamper-resistant records of sensitive access and policy decisions.

## Mandatory
- Log sensitive data access events with actor, action, purpose, target class, outcome, timestamp.
- Redact or tokenize personal data fields before writing logs.
- Protect log integrity and restrict log access to authorized roles.
- Monitor for anomalous access patterns and alert on policy violations.

## Observability Rules
- Error tracking/tracing must disable default PII collection unless explicitly approved.
- Security-relevant events must be searchable and retained per policy class.

## Release Blockers
- Missing audit coverage for protected endpoints.
- Unredacted personal/health data in telemetry payloads.
